Because at the end of the day, the origin of most of the value is as follows:

Bored Apes: The meme
Punks: The meme
Nouns: The meme

The ‚Äúhow‚Äù is where they differ. 15/

So it‚Äôs kind of cool to see three blue chip projects with very different approaches on a key issue. 

There are trade offs and clear philosophical difference (which are super important to many people), but all can theoretically hold value (I‚Äôve personally bet big on it). 14/

Nouns are even more purely embracing that philosophy. 

The CC0 approach takes value from memes as a given and says, ‚Äúhave at it, world.‚Äù 

Our memes are maximized by being culturally relevant, so why not remove the biggest barrier to getting it out there. 13/

This stamp isn‚Äôt worth $8m bc the owner can put it on shirts and sell them. 

It‚Äôs $8m because of its significance in culture and that it is cool to own. 

That‚Äôs CryptoPunks, and that‚Äôs most Bored Apes. 12/

https://t.co/KcGndrcJea

So what are CryptoPunks? They are the purest memes of them all. They are collectibles, analogous to the physical collectibles that have existed throughout history. 

Owning a 1st edition Charizard Pok√©mon card didn‚Äôt let you use Charizard in your business. 11/

But that feels low probability.

The value of most Apes will come from being recognizable as high-value, culturally-relevant goods and not from their individual business potential. 

They are memes more than businesses. 10/

It‚Äôd be BEYOND cool if the #BAYC became an umbrella brand for thousands of individual ape brands. 

Like next f***ing level. 

I hope that materializes. 9/
But while @LarvaLabs is the only one that can make money with the Punks IP currently, it‚Äôs worth asking to what extent that matters in practice. 8/ https://t.co/6xCLnbBlMl
Note: Shoutout @cathsimard_ for her super innovative #FreeHawaiiPhoto from this summer and @gmoneyNFT for being the buyer, releasing the photo to CC0 while compensating @cathsimard_ for her work. 7/

The @nounsdao structure has taken another (awesome) extreme, where all the IP is released to Creative Commons. 

You can make a business around your NFT‚Äôs IP, but so can everyone else. 

Feels a little strange initially. 6/

The BAYC structure let‚Äôs NFT owners build using the characters in their NFTs. 

Most don‚Äôt, but you can, and that 1) incentivizes making a brand out of your Ape and 2) creates a possible real business with cash flows. 4/

To many, the gold standard is what @yugalabs did with @BoredApeYC. 

Ownership gives you full commercial rights over your ape. 

Put them in a book? Go for it. Music video? Hell yeah. And collect those royalties on it. @jenkinsthevalet is crushing this. 3/

There‚Äôs a lot of great discussion these days on which IP rights should be conferred with NFT ownership. 

Full commercial rights? None at all? CC0? 2/
